google_place.adr_address: 1271 Boylston St, Boston, MA 02215, USA
google_place.name: Hojoko

reviews.text: Anyone complaining about the price needs to realize where they are and the type of restaurant they are in. I decided to try brains for the first time here. Absolutely delicious. I always say don't knock it till you try it. I also had their salmon sushi. The rolls fell apart slightly but tasted good. After my meal I realized why they charge $12 for a drink. I left with a wonderful buzz and no mad cow disease from the boiled brains. I say that's worth a rant and a rave. Would recommend to anyone who'd like to try something new.

Just grabbed a few drinks here. Super cool idea and atmosphere. Hipster spot all the way. We enjoyed all the different areas to hang out. Although there was some type of incense or something burning the whole time that was a little too strong. Other than that a really cool place to grab a drink or bite to eat.

Honestly I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of the food considering most fusion restaurants butcher both cultures that it's trying to "fuse". My only gripe is that the food isn't really worth the price! A couple of shrimp and rice cakes for $14? Don't expect to get full very quickly. Would recommend the okonomiyaki though! It's surprisingly well done.

Super cool atmosphere with great food and drink selection. Small plates are definitely small though so I would recommend ordering 3 things per person. The sashimi bowl was very tasty as were the calves brains and shrimp sushi roll. The service was also great, attentive and friendly. I would recommend this for dinner and drinks.
Great cause it was opened late, like wicked late. But the food was mediocre... Very small menu also. I don't know if it was cause we went late or if that was the full menu

google_place.adr_address: 7 Sanborn Ct, Somerville, MA 02143, USA
google_place.name: Backbar

reviews.text: Great little place off the beaten path. Check out the cocktail of the day and the cocktail of the week to try something new. The bartenders are very knowledgeable and friendly. The food is also really good. The bar is super tiny so keeping your group to 4 or less is probably the best. It gets busy on the weekends so going early or during the week is also a smart choice.
Nerd themed speak easy with fantastic mixed drinks. The menu is creative and regularly changes, and the bartenders are creative. They serve some of the best flips that I've had in the area.

Went here for my first drink with my family and we all loved it. Considering the fact it was 5:30 on a Friday, the day before St Patrick's day, I was thinking it was going to be crowded like every other bar I saw. Boy was I wrong! There were a few people at the bar and my family sat on the couch and relaxed as we talked and sipped our drinks. Our server Joe was very friendly and let us take our time with the menu and helped my sister pick which drink she wanted. In conclusion, me and my family had a really good time, made some memories and definitely want to go back there next time we're in Boston.
Tough to get into; small place and often a wait. The drinks are creative and interesting though, and pretty good. Definitely a more unique drink menu than other spots in the area.

Overrated. I feel like this place has a lot of hype and it’s hard to live up to it. Service was good. The drinks were good but nothing special. Small space so crowded and the acoustics were poor. $12 drinks. Epitome of somerville fancy hipster.

google_place.adr_address: 1271 Boylston St, Boston, MA 02215-3410, USA
google_place.name: The Verb Hotel

reviews.text: Very cool vibes at the verb. Right next door to fenway. So if you don't like noisy pick elsewhere. My rooms peephole was blacked out which I found odd. The vent in the bathroom did not work which made it steamy. Everything else was super cool. Selection of records near the lobby if your into that kind of thing. I was pleased with the preselected records already in my room. Someone has good taste! I would recommend this place just for the uniqueness.

Perfect location by Fenway and House of Blues. A bit campy, but the music theme is pretty fun. I love the vinyl library you can borrow from for the record player in your room. Not really a four star hotel when it comes to the rooms, but the location and vibe of the place makes it a great place to have a good time for a night or two.  Oh, and it has a pool! Be warned: it can be kind of a maze trying to find your room.

It was nice to be right in the middle of Fenway area, the rooms were small but comfortable and it was really need having a record player and a record collection to choose from! Employees were super friendly and the food was good although I wish it has been made clear to me that there was no room service ahead of time. It wasn't that much of a hassle to walk down to the bar to pick up the food though

If anyone is looking for great deals on hotels go to HotelRaven.  com Booked a room on there and they had the best rates around...

This hotel is amazing. Using a space that was clearly outdated and making it amazing. It has a great vibe and theme and is now among my favorite boutique hotels. Amazingly located in the city at a fair price. I would highly recommend staying here, especially if you're in town for a musical event like I was. I would recommend they bring it to the next level and start to theme every room and make the records in that room relate to that theme and the decorations match.

Kind staff and clean. I truly did enjoy the hotel and the design of it. The beds where a little stiff and in the morning I did not enjoy hearing the landscapers blowing the leaf blower. I would definitely stay here again without a doubt.

reviews.text: Great quick stop! Just about has all the food you would get at a Stop and Shop, but smaller! Easy to get in and out, and the food is goooood!
Top quality food at a very fair price
The service is great. The selection is great. The sandwich and butcher counter is awesome and accommodating.
Good food everything is good
Best egg salad!
